div.p: LRU is immune because it is a stack algorithm. In stack algorithms, the set of pages in memory with $k$ frames is always a subset of pages in memory with $k+1$ frames: $S(k) \subseteq S(k+1)$

FIFO violates this property. In the 4-frame trace above, at step 7, VPN 1 is evicted because it was the first loaded (at Step 1). However, in the 3-frame trace, VPN 1 was evicted earlier (Step 4) and re-loaded (Step 5), making it "fresher" in the FIFO queue for steps 8 and 9.

g.text: Divergence begins: 4-frame pool holds VPN 1 longer
Anomaly result: 3-frame pool hits cached VPN 1
